  TOMBSTONE - APIM was removed from the CLIQUE Pix architecture on 2026-07-05.

  This file previously held the API-scope policy for "CliquePix API v1" on
  apim-cliquepix-003 (Basic v2). By removal time the only live policy was the
  CORS block for https://clique-pix.com + http://localhost:5173 - i.e. the
  service had become a ~$148/month CORS header. It was removed in the July
  2026 FinOps pass.

  Where things live now:
  - CORS source of truth: Function App platform CORS on func-cliquepix-fresh
    (az functionapp cors show -g rg-cliquepix-prod -n func-cliquepix-fresh).
    Allowed origins: https://clique-pix.com and http://localhost:5173.
    allow-credentials remains false. The old expose-headers x-request-id was
    intentionally not replicated - clients read request_id from the response
    body, never the header.
  - Routing: client -> Front Door (api.clique-pix.com) -> func-cliquepix-fresh.
    No gateway in between.
  - Abuse protection: unchanged - it was already application-layer only
    (JWT validation, membership checks, User Delegation SAS expiry, orphan
    cleanup, per-user video cap). APIM added nothing here since 2026-04-27.

  HISTORY: this file's git history preserves the full six-incident record of
  APIM rate-limiting failures (2026-04-27 x4, 2026-04-29, 2026-05-05) and the
  reasoning for removing rate-limit/quota at all four APIM scopes. Read it
  with: git log -p - - apim_policy.xml   (remove the space between the dashes;
  a literal double-dash cannot appear inside an XML comment - the exact
  footgun documented in HANDOFF.md section 6, which has bitten this repo twice.)

  The don't-regress lesson survives APIM itself: if any gateway or rate
  limiter is ever re-introduced, load-test limits against real traffic
  patterns (5-layer token refresh, 30s polling, retry storms) BEFORE
  enabling. See docs/BETA_OPERATIONS_RUNBOOK.md section 2 (historical) and
  docs/DEPLOYMENT_STATUS.md 2026-07-05 entry.
